properties.Name: PersonalCollectionContact
properties.Description:
A collection attempt or contact that is performed in person with the customer.

Personal contact with customers is likely to ensure that bills get paid.
Small businesses typically do this sort of collections work better because they have a better, more intimate knowledge of their customers.

Prior to a contact the staff person should learn as much about the customer as possible, such as payment habits, who has signing authority over invoices and past collection efforts.

Columns.Name: CollectionEventId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a collection event.

Columns.Name: ContactDescription
Columns.Description: A description of the personal collection contact.

Columns.Name: OutstandingAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of debt outstanding at the time of the personal contact.

Columns.Name: PlannedFollowupCollectionActivityDate
Columns.Description: The date of the planned followup activity.

Columns.Name: PersonalCollectionContactTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Personal Collection Contact Type.

Columns.Name: FollowupCollectionActivityId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Followup Collection Activity Type.
